cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with geometric covering and packing problems for bounded regions on the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problems studied in the paper are NP-hard, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also provides approximation algorithms, which may indicate that it belongs to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
